00:52:55.410 --> 00:52:58.680
because grad students tend
not to be parkers so we

00:52:58.680 --> 00:53:02.520
don't have that bargaining?

00:53:02.520 --> 00:53:06.530
GABRIEL
SANCHEZ-MARTINEZ: That is

00:53:06.530 --> 00:53:10.520
sort of a reason for why they
shouldn't or wouldn't, but I'm

00:53:10.520 --> 00:53:13.010
not sure that it is
the actual reason.

00:53:13.010 --> 00:53:16.460
I think this was always
conceived as an employee

00:53:16.460 --> 00:53:17.800
benefits program.

00:53:17.800 --> 00:53:19.680
AUDIENCE: Aren't
we like employees?

00:53:19.680 --> 00:53:21.180
GABRIEL SANCHEZ-MARTINEZ:
Not quite.

00:53:21.180 --> 00:53:22.970
So yeah.

00:53:22.970 --> 00:53:26.210
So I don't really know
the actual reason.

00:53:26.210 --> 00:53:28.520
Sometimes decisions
are made for--

00:53:28.520 --> 00:53:32.000
you justify them in all sorts of
