So tickets are they're
printed on paper

01:03:50.030 --> 01:03:51.380
and they have a magnetic stripe.

01:03:51.380 --> 01:03:53.710
They don't have a
computer in them.

01:03:53.710 --> 01:03:55.700
The magnetic stripe
holds information

01:03:55.700 --> 01:03:59.550
that can be encrypted.

01:03:59.550 --> 01:04:02.390
So it can be, but it's
not always encrypted.

01:04:02.390 --> 01:04:08.000
It's a little easier for there
to be fraud with tickets.

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:12.167
So if there are
questions on tickets,

01:04:12.167 --> 01:04:13.250
I'll talk more about them.

01:04:13.250 --> 01:04:15.530
Smart cards I've talked about.

01:04:15.530 --> 01:04:17.030
Mobile ticketing
is another option.

01:04:17.030 --> 01:04:19.340
So that's a recent development.

01:04:19.340 --> 01:04:26.690
You have an app, you pay
for a ticket for your ride

01:04:26.690 --> 01:04:27.470
on the app.

01:04:27.470 --> 01:04:30.560
And it's usually kind of
a proof of payment system

01:04:30.560 --> 01:04:35.630
where a fare inspector comes
along and scans a QR code

01:04:35.630 --> 01:04:39.770
on the app, proving that
you've purchased a valid fare

01:04:39.770 --> 01:04:42.140
for that OD pair, for example.

01:04:42.140 --> 01:04:44.600
This is being used here in
commuter rail in Boston.

01:04:47.580 --> 01:04:51.980
And then the sort of newest
form is contactless bank cards.

01:04:51.980 --> 01:04:58.330
So that's a wireless Visa,
MasterCard, credit charge card,

01:04:58.330 --> 01:05:03.060
debit card and you
tap it on the--

01:05:03.060 --> 01:05:04.470
there you go.

01:05:04.470 --> 01:05:07.610
You can pass it if you want.

01:05:07.610 --> 01:05:08.190
Can I see it?

01:05:12.360 --> 01:05:14.160
So you tap it just
like you would

01:05:14.160 --> 01:05:17.550
a Charlie card or an
Oyster card in London

01:05:17.550 --> 01:05:24.450
and there's the dialogue
between the fare and the card.

01:05:24.450 --> 01:05:26.950
Strong encryption.

01:05:26.950 --> 01:05:29.640
As I said, the full
validation process

01:05:29.640 --> 01:05:33.120
doesn't always happen,
especially in bus,

01:05:33.120 --> 01:05:34.864
because you can trust the card.

01:05:34.864 --> 01:05:36.030
There is a separate antenna.

01:05:36.030 --> 01:05:38.820
Of course, the frequencies and
the protocols are different.

01:05:38.820 --> 01:05:40.380
But there are good
standards for this

01:05:40.380 --> 01:05:43.890
and London has moved to this.

01:05:43.890 --> 01:05:46.860
CTA's system is based
on this technology,

01:05:46.860 --> 01:05:54.890
even though they opted
to only use token cards.

01:05:54.890 --> 01:05:56.500
So it's the same
technology, but it's

01:05:56.500 --> 01:05:58.070
branded as their own thing.

01:05:58.070 --> 01:06:00.850
And I don't know if they can--

01:06:00.850 --> 01:06:01.810
now it does, right?

01:06:01.810 --> 01:06:03.229
But at the beginning, it wasn't.

01:06:03.229 --> 01:06:05.020
AUDIENCE: I met someone
